Check a c =cosθ *cosθ=cos²θ. But from above, a c = -1 +2 cos2θ. So, cos²θ = -1 +2 cos2θ. But cos2θ=2 cos²θ -1. Substitute: cos²θ = -1 +2*(2 cos²θ -1)= -1 +4 cos²θ -2=4 cos²θ -3. Bring all terms to left: cos²θ -4 cos²θ +3=0 => -3 cos²θ +3=0 => -3 cos²θ = -3 => cos²θ=1 => cosθ=±1. Therefore, this factorization is possible only if cosθ=±1. Which would mean ��=0 or π.
